Plans to use it to vaccinate health workers were scrapped after a study showed "disappointing" results against the new Covid-19 variant in the country. Instead it is intending to use the Johnson & Johnson vaccine. South Africa has one and half million doses of the AstraZeneca jab and is now considering what to do with them. "There are already some countries that are asking that we must sell it to them," South Africa's Health Minister, Zweli Mkhize, told a news conference on Wednesday. But he said that he will wait for experts' conclusions before making a decision. "Our scientists will continue with further deliberations on the AstraZeneca vaccine used in South Africa and depending on their advice the vaccine will be swapped before the expiry date." He added that he was due to speak with the World Health Organisation) shortly after the news conference. --BBC--